OL,3,CHope for child contact centre
OL,4,Cfollowing government u-turn
OL,6,FJersey's only child contact centre has
OL,7,Fbeen saved from closure following a
OL,8,Fgovernment u-turn.
OL,10,FLocal childcare charity Centrepoint
OL,11,Fwas given #81,000 by Jersey's States
OL,12,Fin 2023 to open and operate the
OL,13,Fcentre, which provides a safe space
OL,14,Ffor parents to meet with their
OL,15,Fchildren if they don't have custody.
OL,17,FLast month they announced that money
OL,18,Fhad run out and they were facing the
OL,19,Fprospect of imminent closure - leaving
OL,20,Fthe 17 families currently supported by
OL,21,Fthe charity without anywhere to go.
